<LOCATION> Fianarantsoa </LOCATION> in the south. In Reunion, a <LOCATION> French </LOCATION> overseas territory, the pope will meet with <LOCATION> French </LOCATION> Prime Minister <PERSON> Michel </PERSON> <PERSON> Rocard </PERSON> and beatify a 19th century <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> school teacher who helped abolish slavery on the island. In a papal first, <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> will fly on the Concorde, but the <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> France </ORGANIZATION> jetliner that will take him to <LOCATION> Zambia </LOCATION> will not travel at supersonic speed because of the shortness of the trip. In <LOCATION> Zambia </LOCATION>, headquarters of the <ORGANIZATION> African </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION>, the <PERSON> pope </PERSON> is expected to speak about apartheid in <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION>, the system of racial segregation which the <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> recently denounced as the most systematic form of racism in the world. In <LOCATION> Malawi </LOCATION>, the pope may raise the issue of AIDS, which has afflicted some 20 percent of the male population, the <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> officials said.
