<HEAD>Bloody Night in Copenhagen</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COPENHAGEN, Denmark (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Five people, including a child, were slain in one of the bloodiest nights on record in the Danish capital, national TV reported Friday. Police believe a 27-year-old man went on a rampage and killed three women and a young girl before he committed suicide in a rented car. One of the women and the little girl were found murdered in the man's apartment Friday morning. Police said they had a `` family relationship'' with the man. Police also discovered the body of a 30-year-old woman who was shot to death in her home while her family slept in another part of the house. Around the same time, a woman in her 20s was found stabbed to death in an apartment after neighbors called police about a disturbance. Police later found the man in a car parked nearby, and they said he had shot himself. Police also connected the man with two attempted murders Thursday. In the fifth, unrelated slaying, an elderly man was stabbed to death in his apartment. A 20-year-old prostitute was arrested in the slaying. No identities were released.
