name</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By LISA M. HAMM</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 City police and federal agents seized 20 weapons, including a grenade launcher, and arrested six people in a raid on a motel in the capital's northeast section early today. A Nazi flag was found in one of two cars with <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> license plates searched during the raid, said <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Kelso </PERSON>, assistant special agent in charge of the <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION>'s <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> field office. The investigation started Thursday afternoon when a suburban <LOCATION> Dallas </LOCATION> woman called the <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION>'s <LOCATION> Dallas </LOCATION> field office to report that her son, <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Barnhart </PERSON>, 33, of <LOCATION> Rowlette </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>, had been kidnapped. The unidentified woman said <PERSON> Barnhart </PERSON>, who had been missing two weeks, instructed her to wire him $ 1,000 here or `` some harm would come to him,'' according to <PERSON> Kelso </PERSON>. <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> agents traced the man to the motel and quickly determined that he had n't been kidnapped, <PERSON> Kelso </PERSON> said. `` Apparently they may have been low on funds and this may have been an effort by him to get some additional funds,'' <PERSON> Kelso </PERSON> said. `` It's unfortunate that he would involve his mother.'' <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> agents discovered the hotel rooms contained automatic weapons and notified city police, the <ORGANIZATION> Secret </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> Bureau </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Alcohol </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> , </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tobacco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Firearms </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> official said. Two of the suspects _ <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON>