<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION>, which last November acknowledged that it had been flying the stealth fighter at night for five years, has started operating the F-117A jets during the day, said a report published Friday. Aviation Week and Space Technology reported in its May 1 edition that over the past two weeks, as many as 20 stealth fighters have been spotted over <LOCATION> Mojave </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>, near <ORGANIZATION> Edwards </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> Base. The weekly magazine published a grainy color photograph of an airborne F-117A, but it was far less detailed than a picture released by the <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> last November when it acknowledged the existence of the airplane for the first time. More than 50 of the swept-wing twin engine warplanes are stationed at the <LOCATION> Tonopah </LOCATION> Test Range Air Field in <LOCATION> Nevada </LOCATION>. They are attached to the <ORGANIZATION> 4450th </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tactical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> at <ORGANIZATION> Nellis </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Base </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> said in statement last Nov. 10. Capt. <PERSON> Susan </PERSON> <PERSON> Strednansky </PERSON>, an <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> spokeswoman at the Pentagon, said she had no information about daylight flights of the F-117A, but noted that the November announcement signaled that such operations were imminent. `` Daytime flights have been available to them since we released their existence,'' said <PERSON> Strednansky </PERSON>. `` If you fly it only at night, you can not integrate it into the rest of the <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION>.'' Fifty-nine stealth fighters are being purchased from the <ORGANIZATION> Lockheed </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> at an undisclosed price, she said. Aviation Week, quoting unidentified residents of <LOCATION> Mojave </LOCATION>, said the fighters were flying what appeared to be training missions at 5:30 p.m. and 10:30 p.m. Local residents, many of whom are aerospace workers, say the F-117A makes an unsual noise, `` a distinctive, although faint, engine whine'' that the magazine said may be caused by an unusal design to the air intake. The stealth fighter, like the B-2 stealth bomber now under development, is triangular in shape and incorporates design features and material intended to make it all but invisible to enemy targeting radar. The trailing edge of the wings is sawtooth in shape, to avoid presenting right-angles to enemy radar, Aviation Week reported. When the <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> disclosed the existence of the F-117A last November, it said the plane was first flown in June 1981 and had been in operation since 1983.
