<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Cards, calls and compassion were pouring in Friday for the desperate young father who held hospital workers at gunpoint as he removed his comatose baby son from life-support systems and held him till he died. <PERSON> Rudy </PERSON> <PERSON> Linares </PERSON>, 23, a house painter from west suburban <PERSON> Cicero </PERSON>, faces first-degree murder charges in the death early Wednesday of his 16-month-old son, <PERSON> Samuel </PERSON>. `` I would fly to <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> tomorrow ... and do anything I could to help this guy because I feel that there but for the grace of God go I,'' <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Killigrew </PERSON>, parent of a brain-damaged child, said from <LOCATION> Nevada </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Samuel </PERSON> had been in a coma, partially brain dead, since he swallowed a balloon at an Aug. 2 birthday party, blocking the flow of oxygen to his brain The toddler was considered to be in a `` irreversible vegetative coma,'' says Dr. <PERSON> Gilbert </PERSON> <PERSON> Goldman </PERSON>, <PERSON> Samuel </PERSON>'s physician at pediatric intensive care at Rush-Presbyterian-St. <PERSON> Luke </PERSON>'s Medical Center <PERSON> Goldman </PERSON> has said he did not believe he could legally comply with the family's request months ago for withdrawal of life support though he was `` personally and professionally sympathetic.'' Under state child-abuse laws, support could be withdrawn only if <PERSON> Samuel </PERSON> had been found to be totally brain-dead or his heart and lungs had stopped functioning, said <PERSON> Max </PERSON> <PERSON> Brown </PERSON>, a lawyer for the hospital. The family had planned to see a lawyer Friday to discuss their options. `` This is something that should not be the choice of government, it's a private individual's choice,'' <PERSON> Killigrew </PERSON> said in a telephone interview with The <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION>