Beach </LOCATION>. `` I feel pretty good so far,'' <PERSON> Richardson </PERSON> told reporters. `` I have n't made any plans at this time but to be with Mr. <PERSON> Dick </PERSON> <PERSON> Gregory </PERSON>. I think it's going to be wonderful.'' <PERSON> Richardson </PERSON> is to spend the weekend at the clinic. <PERSON> Gregory </PERSON> has offered a $ 100,000-a-year job at the diet clinic to the 53-year-old former orange picker, who has until June 1 to decide on a contract, said <PERSON> Richardson </PERSON> attorney <PERSON> Ellis </PERSON> <PERSON> Rubin </PERSON>. <PERSON> Richardson </PERSON> also will work with the <ORGANIZATION> Southern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Christian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Leadership </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Conference </ORGANIZATION> in its programs against drug and alcohol abuse and will counsel prison inmates, <PERSON> Gregory </PERSON> said, praising <PERSON> Richardson </PERSON> for his loving attitude. `` I can not believe that this man ... is not bitter,'' <PERSON> Gregory </PERSON> said. `` If he was bitter, I could sympathize with him, but I would n't hire him.'' <PERSON> Richardson </PERSON> sat before King's tomb and sang out the words on the slain civil rights leader's crypt: `` Free at last, free at last, thank God almighty, I'm free.'' <PERSON> Richardson </PERSON> used the same words on the first full day of his release. <ORGANIZATION> SCLC </ORGANIZATION> President <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Lowery </PERSON> said <PERSON> Richardson </PERSON>'s case `` underscores and affirms, again and again, the argument against the death penalty. One of the damnable things about the death penalty is you can not correct a mistake. He would be dead.'' <PERSON> Richardson </PERSON>'s death sentence was commuted to a life term in 1972 after the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> struck down the nation's capital punishment laws. <PE