<HEAD>Garrison Chosen CEO For New Thiokol Inc.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> U. </PERSON> <PERSON> Edwin </PERSON> <PERSON> Garrison </PERSON> has been selected president and chief executive officer of the new <ORGANIZATION> Thiokol </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, the company to be formed when <ORGANIZATION> Morton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Thiokol </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>'s aerospace and specialty chemical divisions are separated. Garrison, 61, will be joined at the head of the new company by <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> T. </PERSON> <PERSON> Marsh </PERSON>, 64, a retired <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> general who was named chairman of <ORGANIZATION> Thiokol </ORGANIZATION>'s new board of directors, said spokesman <PERSON> Nancy </PERSON> <PERSON> Hobor </PERSON>. <PERSON> Marsh </PERSON> is now a member of <ORGANIZATION> Morton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Thiokol </ORGANIZATION>'s board. Pending stockholder approval, <ORGANIZATION> Morton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Thiokol </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> will split to become <ORGANIZATION> Morton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Thiokol </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> on July 1. <ORGANIZATION> Morton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> will contain the commercial businesses of specialty chemicals, air bags for auto mobiles and salt. The split, proposed in late March, was described by industry analysts as a move to separate two diverse business operations. <ORGANIZATION> Thiokol </ORGANIZATION> will include the company's aerospace operations. <ORGANIZATION> Morton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Thiokol </ORGANIZATION> employs 8,000 people in <LOCATION> Utah </LOCATION>, mostly at operations west of <LOCATION> Brigham </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> and at aerospace division headquarters in <LOCATION> Ogden </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Morton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Thiokol </ORGANIZATION> is based in <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION>, which will remain the corporate home of the new <ORGANIZATION> Morton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> S. </PERSON> <PERSON> Locke </PERSON>, who is now chairman of <ORGANIZATION> Morton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Thiokol </ORGANIZATION>, will become chairman and chief executive officer of <ORGANIZATION> Morton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> Garrison is now president of the <ORGANIZATION> Aerospace </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Morton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Thiokol </ORGANIZATION>, and is the corporation's vice president, positions he assumed in 1983. A graduate of <ORGANIZATION> Mississippi </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> and a native of <LOCATION> Alabama </LOCATION>, he lives in <LOCATION> Ogden </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Marsh </PERSON> retired from the <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> in 1984. In addition to <PERSON> Morton </PERSON> <PERSON> Thiokol </PERSON>, he serves on the boards of <ORGANIZATION> Cimflex </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Teknowledge </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> CAE </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Link </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> ITHACO </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and as a trustee of <ORGANIZATION> MITRE </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp </ORGANIZATION>. He lives in <LOCATION> Alexandria </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Va </LOCATION>.
