<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The maverick buyout firm <ORGANIZATION> Kohlberg </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Kravis </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Roberts </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> said today it has completed its record $ 24.53 billion acquisition of <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nabisco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>. Trading in the company's stock on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> was to cease at the end of the day The completion of the deal that stunned Wall Street came a day after shareholders formally approved the buyout at a special meeting in <LOCATION> Wilmington </LOCATION>, Del. Company officials said about 85 percent of <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nabisco </ORGANIZATION>'s shares were voted in favor of the merger. Separately, <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nabisco </ORGANIZATION> announced Thursday that it would move its headquarters from <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION> to the <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> area by the end of the year so the food-and-tobacco giant can be in close contact with the financial community. The company will decide over the next few weeks whether layoffs are necessary, said <PERSON> Pauline </PERSON> <PERSON> Howes </PERSON>, an <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nabisco </ORGANIZATION> spokeswoman. About 450 <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nabisco </ORGANIZATION> employees work in <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION>, she said. The move would be the second for <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nabisco </ORGANIZATION> corporate headquarters in recent years. Former RJR President <PERSON> F. </PERSON> <PERSON> Ross </PERSON> <PERSON> Johnson </P