<HEAD>Parent Of Bloomingdale's and Other Chain Stores Restructures</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MARYBETH NIBLEY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>'s board of directors Friday announced a realignment that establishes <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> as a holding company for its real estate and retailing operations in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Canada </LOCATION>. The restructuring of the Toronto-based corporation came as the result of a process that has been in the works since <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> acquired <ORGANIZATION> Federated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stores </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> in a $ 6.7 billion hostile takeover last May. <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Campeau </PERSON> will continue as chairman and chief executive. <PERSON> Ronald </PERSON> <PERSON> W. </PERSON> <PERSON> Tysoe </PERSON>, formerly executive vice president and president of <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> -LRB- <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> -RRB-, will take over as president and chief operating officer of the newly restructured company. <PERSON> Tysoe </PERSON> replaces <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> T. </PERSON> <PERSON> Roddy </PERSON>, whose resignation was disclosed Thursday. <PERSON> Roddy </PERSON>, 45, and a veteran of the retail business, worked closely on the takeover of <PERSON> Federated </PERSON>. There was no word on <PERSON> Roddy </PERSON>'s plans and an announcement Friday from <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> said only that he was leaving to pursue other career interests. <PERSON> Carolyn </PERSON> <PERSON> Buck </PERSON> <PERSON> Luce </PERSON>, a <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> senior vice president who had been involved with financial nuts and bolts of the Federated purchase, also submitted her resignation. Retail industry analysts said the changes in the corporate parent should have little direct bearing on <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION>'s department store businesses. <PERSON> Federated </PERSON> operates <PERSON> Abraham </PERSON> and <PERSON> Straus </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Bloomingdale </ORGANIZATION>'s, <LOCATION> Burdines </LOCATION> and other chain stores. Also under <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION>'s corporate umbrella is <ORGANIZATION> Allied </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stores </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, which <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> acquired in 1986 for $ 3.4 billion. Allied and <PERSON> Federated </PERSON> have headquarters in <LOCATION> Cincinnati </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Pamela </PERSON> <PERSON> Stubing </PERSON>, an analyst with <ORGANIZATION> Moody </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Investors </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, said the changes at <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> could end up being beneficial for Allied and <PERSON> Federated </PERSON>. `` I'm told that ... the people at the Allied-Federated level will have more say in day-to-day operations and strategies going forward,'' said <PERSON> Stubing </PERSON>. `` I think that's good. There's always a danger when there are decisions being made one level removed.'' She said <ORGANIZATION> Moody </ORGANIZATION>'s does n't intend to initiate a review of the ratings it has assigned to Allied and <PERSON> Federated </PERSON> debt on account of <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION>'s restructuring. <ORGANIZATION> Moody </ORGANIZATION>'s is a leading credit rating agency and its opinions can influence the interest rates corporations are charged to borrow money. `` I'm just waiting for the second half of the year to see how that transpires,'' she said, noting that the second six months of the calendar year is the most important time for retailers. <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> said the reorganization `` reflects the evolution'' that began in 1985 with `` our decision to grow beyond our Canadian real estate roots and to acquire certain prime <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> retail interests.'' `` We have made tremendous progress in the last year in accomplishing our strategies for asset acquisition and restructuring, as well as debt reduction and corporate financing,'' the company stated. Under the restructuring, separate subsidiaries will report to the <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> holding company. These are: <PERSON> Federated </PERSON> and Allied, which together form the department store group; <ORGANIZATION> Ralphs </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Grocery </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, the <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> supermarket unit; <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Development </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> real estate group; and <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Canada </ORGANIZATION>, the Canadian real estate development concern. Two additional executive changes were announced. <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> Campbell </PERSON>, currently senior vice president for the Eastern region of <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, has been named president of the restructured <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Canada </ORGANIZATION>, which comprises all of the company's commercial real estate and shopping center interests in <LOCATION> Canada </LOCATION> <PERSON> Russell </PERSON> <PERSON> S. </PERSON> <PERSON> Davis </PERSON>, executive vice president and chief financial officer of <PERSON> Federated </PERSON> and Allied, will expand his responsibilities and also become chief financial officer for the <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> holding company. He succeeds <PERSON> Roger </PERSON> <PERSON> Ashton </PERSON> who resigned to return to a partnership position at a <LOCATION> Toronto </LOCATION> accounting firm. In a separate announcement, <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> repor