dollars, down from 1.1940. Gold prices slumped worldwide. On the Commodity Exchange in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, gold bullion for current delivery fell to $ 377.90 a troy ounce, from Wednesday's $ 383.30. The late bid gold price in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> was $ 378.25 a troy ounce, down from $ 384.25. The <LOCATION> Zurich </LOCATION>, late bid price was $ 377.75, down from $ 384.25. Earlier in <LOCATION> Hong </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Kong </LOCATION>, gold closed at $ 381.85 bid, down from $ 385.15. Silver bullion prices also slipped. On the <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Comex </LOCATION>, silver bullion for current delivery settled at $ 5.601 a troy ounce, down from Thursday's close of $ 5.645. In <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>, silver traded at a late bid price of $ 5.63 a troy ounce, down from $ 5.76.
